/* History */Is there any other source/book/article that mentions them as Rajputs ? No. They are Rajputs according to the perspective of just one writer who does not even belong to the region or the country. Tons of books written in various languages have confirmed that they are not Rajputs. So it’s better to remove the word without causing further confusion to the readers.
/* 1675–1947 (from Jeypore) */Added name of the current heir in the table.

/* Post-independence titular king */The government and judiciary of India has shown support to such events and most of the coronations are attended by government officials too. So, if the Indian government, judiciary and people do not have a problem then it shows that these events and titles are still respected and taken fairly in the country.
